# Line-ending policy.
#
# GitHub's Windows runner images ship with core.autocrlf=true. Without the rules
# below that setting breaks the test suite in two independent ways:
#
#   * every tests/*.sh is checked out with CRLF, so bash fails on the shebang
#     line with "$'\r': command not found" before running a single assertion;
#   * every tests/golden/* fixture is checked out with CRLF while apiary writes
#     its output through llvm::raw_fd_ostream in binary (LF) mode, so each
#     golden diff fails with a whole-file mismatch that reads like a codegen
#     regression but is purely a checkout artifact.
#
# Normalizing to LF in the index and on checkout everywhere avoids both.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Byte-exactness matters most for these two categories, so state it explicitly
# rather than relying on text=auto's heuristic.
*.sh                text eol=lf
tests/golden/**     text eol=lf
*.golden            text eol=lf
